      "content": "that makes sense, but if the goal is just to follow what they originally meant, how do originalists deal with the fact that society has changed so much? like, if the founders didn't imagine things like the internet or modern privacy rights, doesn't following their specific intent end up being a way to block progress or just apply outdated, potentially biased views to the modern world? isn't that why people say it's more about keeping power where it was in the 1700s?",
